  		<div class="item2">
  		
  		<p>Physicians diagnose and treat conditions and illnesses with medication rather than operations. 
  		<p>After their first few years as a junior doctor, they go on to specialise in a particular area of medicine.</p>  
  		<p>Some stay in hospital and become specialist consultants like cardiologists (problems of the heart), psychiatrists (problems with mental health) or radiologists (interpreting medical images like x rays and CAT scans).  </p>
  		<p>Others like to look after a wide range people with a variety of health problems and become General Practitioners (GPs).</p>
		
  		
  		
  		
